&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/art/images/2017/ChristmasCards/Six.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Fire Salamander&quot; class=&quot;img-block&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Kyle Thomas Raymond</name></author><category term="art" /><summary type="html"></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">The Devil’s in this Cookie</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/poems/2016/The_Devils_in_this_Cookie" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="The Devil's in this Cookie" /><published>2016-12-12T00:00:00-08:00</published><updated>2016-12-12T00:00:00-08:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/poems/2016/The_Devils_in_this_Cookie</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/poems/2016/The_Devils_in_this_Cookie">&lt;pre&gt;
The devil's in this Cookie
on this plate right next to me.

The cookie's small, the plate is large,
but the devil's all I see.

I heard the devil's whisper:
&quot;Save this little one for last,&quot;
and not three seconds later
I ate its family fast.

Now I sit, my lips a'tremblin',
powdered sugar on my jaw;
the devil's in this cookie.

(pause)

Now...
the devil's me.
&lt;/pre&gt;</content><author><name>Kyle Thomas Raymond</name></author><category term="poems" /><summary type="html">The devil's in this Cookie on this plate right next to me.</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Under the Desert</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/art/2016/SOD" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Under the Desert" /><published>2016-11-22T00:00:00-08:00</published><updated>2016-11-22T00:00:00-08:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/art/2016/SOD</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/art/2016/SOD">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/art/images/SOD_Page_1_small.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;SOD_Page_1&quot; class=&quot;img-block&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

